        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:51PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wirtz, or over Boones Mill, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Vinton...
Boones Mill...
Stewartsville...
Chamblissburg...
Burnt Chimney...
and Hollins.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
